The paper discusses the optimization of coherent group communications in self-organizing wireless networks, which involves joint network formation and beamforming. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the optimization of signal-to-interference-ratio, which is a common problem in control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of single-antenna communication nodes, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for optimizing network performance.
